  - 146
  - 132
By: Mîrâ Bâî
Format: Verse
---
Kâhn have I bought, the price he asked, I gave.
Some cry, ‘Tis great’, and others jeer, ‘ Tis small’ --
I gave in full, weighed to the utmost grain,
My love, my life, my soul, my all.
